Toby Ord's "[Moral Trade](http://www.amirrorclear.net/academic/papers/moral-trade.pdf)" outlines how moral trade might work.

Moral trade is one of several ideas that takes an idea from the for-profit world and creates an analogue in the non-profit world.

When moral trade takes place with oneself, it is just [moral offsetting](Moral offset)^[[Carl\_Shulman comments on What is the expected effect of poverty alleviation efforts on existential risk?](http://effective-altruism.com/ea/oh/what_is_the_expected_effect_of_poverty/586).].
